HyperFrog v36.0 (Connected-Graph Formal Miner, research prototype)
Usage:
  ./hyperfrog --gen-keys <prefix> [--password <pw>] [--mine-mode formal|practical] [--mine-ms <ms>] [--threads <n>] [--min-cycle-rank <g>]
  ./hyperfrog --validate-keys <prefix> [--password <pw>]
  ./hyperfrog --enc <prefix> <in_plain> <out_hf>
  ./hyperfrog --dec <prefix> <in_hf> <out_plain> [--password <pw>]
  ./hyperfrog --test-all
  ./hyperfrog --benchmark <prefix> [--password <pw>] [--iters <n>] [--file-mb <mb>] [--bench-keygen] [--out <outprefix>] [--mine-mode formal|practical] [--require-connected] [--mine-ms <ms>] [--threads <n>] [--min-cycle-rank <g>]
  ./hyperfrog --help

Files:
  <prefix>.pk  public key (seed_A + b); ~4.0 KiB for current params
  <prefix>.sk  secret key (includes pk; optionally password-protected via Argon2id)

Mining:
  Default budget is 30000 ms.
  Mine modes:
    --mine-mode formal    : connected-growth formal miner; exact weight 2048, connected by
                           construction, and accepts only if cycle_rank>=min_cycle_rank.
                           No fallback, no keep-largest-component, no best-of selection.
    --mine-mode practical : engineering miner (keep-largest-component + best-of selection);
                           includes deterministic timeout fallback and is not the formal law.
  NOTE: In formal mode, timeout fails KeyGen (no deterministic fallback).
  Security note: formal mode samples a structured, non-uniform connected-graph exact-weight
                 secret distribution; this code does not claim a reduction to standard
                 binary-secret LWE.

Benchmark:
  Generates <out>.csv and <out>.json plus <out>.bin/.enc/.dec for sanity-check.
  Defaults: --iters 200, --file-mb 64, --out <prefix>.bench (key files: <prefix>.pk/.sk).

Examples:
  ./hyperfrog --gen-keys mykeys --password "hunter2" --mine-ms 5000
  ./hyperfrog --validate-keys mykeys --password "hunter2"
  ./hyperfrog --enc mykeys input.bin output.hf
  ./hyperfrog --dec mykeys output.hf recovered.bin --password "hunter2"
  ./hyperfrog --benchmark mykeys --password "hunter2" --iters 500 --file-mb 128 --bench-keygen

